{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"getFrameClock"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"FrameClockRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3Gdk13FrameClockRefV"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The frame clock is a global “ticker” that can be used to drive"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"animations and repaints. The most common reason to get the frame"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"clock is to call [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.FrameClock.get_frame_time"},{"type":"text","text":"], in order"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to get a time to use for animating. For example you might record"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the start of the animation with an initial value from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.FrameClock.get_frame_time"},{"type":"text","text":"], and then update the animation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by calling [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.FrameClock.get_frame_time"},{"type":"text","text":"] again during each repaint."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.FrameClock.request_phase"},{"type":"text","text":"] will result in a new frame on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"clock, but won’t necessarily repaint any widgets. To repaint a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"widget, you have to use [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.Widget.queue_draw"},{"type":"text","text":"] which invalidates"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the widget (thus scheduling it to receive a draw on the next"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"frame). "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gtk_widget_queue_draw()"},{"type":"text","text":" will also end up requesting a frame"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the appropriate frame clock."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A widget’s frame clock will not change while the widget is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"mapped. Reparenting a widget (which implies a temporary unmap) can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"change the widget’s frame clock."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unrealized widgets do not have a frame clock."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gtk\/mediacontrolsref\/getframeclock()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/MediaControlsRef\/getFrameClock()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Obtains the frame clock for a widget."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"getFrameClock()","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"getFrameClock"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"FrameClockRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3Gdk13FrameClockRefV"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:3Gtk14WidgetProtocolPAAE13getFrameClock3Gdk0eF3RefVSgyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3Gtk16MediaControlsRefV","extendedModule":"Gtk","modules":[{"name":"Gtk"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/MediaControlsRef","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/MediaControlsRef\/WidgetProtocol-Implementations"]]},"references":{"doc://Gtk/documentation/Gtk/MediaControlsRef/getFrameClock()